Dear AZ,

It's coming up to your birthday!

On your 13th birthday, your parents'/guardians' access to your record will automatically be removed.

If you would like to re-invite a parent/guardian as a carer after they have been removed, you can send them an invite in the Sharing section of your record.

This message is to remind you to discuss this with your parents/guardians or clinical team.

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

On AZ Patient 1's 13th birthday, their parents/guardians will automatically be removed as carers from their record. This means that you will no longer have access to their record. From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address. If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation. Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for: http://pkb-frontend-5 Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_990_1754307372.1673396529301 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Bz,

AZ Patient 1 is reaching a milestone!

On AZ Patient 1's 13th birthday, their parents/guardians will automatically be removed as carers from their record. This means that you will no longer have access to their record.

From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address.

If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation.

Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish.

If you are a parent/guardian managing this record for a young person with a learning disability or if you have any other concerns, please contact their clinical team for advice.

You are receiving this notification because you are a carer. To log in and review the people you care for, please click this link: "http://pkb-frontend-5/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Dear AZ,

Happy Birthday!

This message is to remind you that, as it's your 13th birthday, your carer Bz Patient 1 has been automatically removed as a carer and no longer has access to your record.

If you would like to re-invite Bz, you can send them an invite in the Sharing section of your PKB record.

If you have any questions or concerns about this, please discuss it with your parents/guardians or clinical team.

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Dear Bz,

AZ Patient 1 has reached a milestone!

This message is to remind you that, as it's AZ Patient 1's 13th birthday, you have been removed as a carer and no longer have access to their record.

From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address.

If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation.

Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish.

If you are a parent/guardian managing this record for a young person with a learning disability or if you have any other concerns, please contact their clinical team for advice.

You are receiving this notification because you are a carer. To log in and review the people you care for, please click this link: "http://pkb-frontend-5/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Please consider being my carer

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care: http://pkb-frontend-5 Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1018_1402262292.1673396554841 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear AZ,

It's coming up to your birthday!

On your 16th birthday, your parents'/guardians' access to your record will automatically be removed.

If you would like to re-invite a parent/guardian as a carer after they have been removed, you can send them an invite in the Sharing section of your record.

This message is to remind you to discuss this with your parents/guardians or clinical team.

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team


w: http://www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us
e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1018_1402262292.1673396554841-- ------=_Part_1017_2089292627.1673396554841-- ------=_Part_1016_1258233158.1673396554841-- , Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:22:34 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: Bz Patient 2 Message-ID: <920688473.1023.1673396554960@26072c911b4a> Subject: Reminder: changes to access on AZ Patient 1's 16th birthday MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1020_903436106.1673396554956" ------=_Part_1020_903436106.1673396554956 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1021_340379865.1673396554956" ------=_Part_1021_340379865.1673396554956 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1022_1907551494.1673396554956" ------=_Part_1022_1907551494.1673396554956 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Bz, AZ Patient 1 is reaching a milestone! On AZ Patient 1's 16th birthday, their parents/guardians will automatically be removed as carers from their record. This means that you will no longer have access to their record. From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address. If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation. Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish. If you are a parent/guardian managing this record for a young person with a learning disability or if you have any other concerns, please contact their clinical team for advice. You are receiving this notification because you are a carer. To log in and review the people you care for, please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-5/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for: http://pkb-frontend-5 Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1022_1907551494.1673396554956 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Bz,

AZ Patient 1 is reaching a milestone!

On AZ Patient 1's 16th birthday, their parents/guardians will automatically be removed as carers from their record. This means that you will no longer have access to their record.

From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address.

If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation.

Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish.

If you are a parent/guardian managing this record for a young person with a learning disability or if you have any other concerns, please contact their clinical team for advice.

You are receiving this notification because you are a carer. To log in and review the people you care for, please click this link: "http://pkb-frontend-5/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Dear AZ,

Happy Birthday!

This message is to remind you that, as it's your 16th birthday, your carer Bz Patient 2 has been automatically removed as a carer and no longer has access to your record.

If you would like to re-invite Bz, you can send them an invite in the Sharing section of your PKB record.

If you have any questions or concerns about this, please discuss it with your parents/guardians or clinical team.

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Dear Bz,

AZ Patient 1 has reached a milestone!

This message is to remind you that, as it's AZ Patient 1's 16th birthday, you have been removed as a carer and no longer have access to their record.

From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address.

If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation.

Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish.

If you are a parent/guardian managing this record for a young person with a learning disability or if you have any other concerns, please contact their clinical team for advice.

You are receiving this notification because you are a carer. To log in and review the people you care for, please click this link: "http://pkb-frontend-5/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

Dear AZ,

It's coming up to your birthday!

On your 18th birthday, your parents'/guardians' access to your record will automatically be removed.

If you would like to re-invite a parent/guardian as a carer after they have been removed, you can send them an invite in the Sharing section of your record.

This message is to remind you to discuss this with your parents/guardians or clinical team.

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

On AZ Patient 1's 18th birthday, their parents/guardians will automatically be removed as carers from their record. This means that you will no longer have access to their record. From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address. If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation. Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for: http://pkb-frontend-5 Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1054_1747736498.1673396580967 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear AZ,

AZ Patient 1 is reaching a milestone!

On AZ Patient 1's 18th birthday, their parents/guardians will automatically be removed as carers from their record. This means that you will no longer have access to their record.

From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address.

If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation.

Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish.

If you are a parent/guardian managing this record for a young person with a learning disability or if you have any other concerns, please contact their clinical team for advice.

You are receiving this notification because you are a carer. To log in and review the people you care for, please click this link: "http://pkb-frontend-5/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

parameters.value:
[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:23:01 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: az.patient.1@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <1715060457.1059.1673396581126@26072c911b4a> Subject: Your 18th birthday MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1056_1046607605.1673396581123" ------=_Part_1056_1046607605.1673396581123 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1057_1812239973.1673396581123" ------=_Part_1057_1812239973.1673396581123 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1058_259645935.1673396581123" ------=_Part_1058_259645935.1673396581123 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear AZ, Happy Birthday! This message is to remind you that, as it's your 18th birthday, your carer AZ Patient 3 has been automatically removed as a carer and no longer has access to your record. If you would like to re-invite AZ, you can send them an invite in the Sharing section of your PKB record. If you have any questions or concerns about this, please discuss it with your parents/guardians or clinical team. Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care: http://pkb-frontend-5 Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1058_259645935.1673396581123 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear AZ,

Happy Birthday!

Dear AZ,

AZ Patient 1 has reached a milestone!

This message is to remind you that, as it's AZ Patient 1's 18th birthday, you have been removed as a carer and no longer have access to their record.

From the age of 13, young people are encouraged to register for their own record. To do this, they will need their own email address.

If AZ hasn't registered for their own record and has been sent a registration link by email in the past, they can use this to register, otherwise they can request a new invitation.

Once they have registered, they can re-invite you as a carer if they wish.

If you are a parent/guardian managing this record for a young person with a learning disability or if you have any other concerns, please contact their clinical team for advice.

You are receiving this notification because you are a carer. To log in and review the people you care for, please click this link: "http://pkb-frontend-5/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to manage your care and those whom you care for.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team
